In lilary’s reign he obtained a Prebend of Chichester, but on Elizabeth's accession he retired with his parents to Louvahr, whither, after an excur- sion to France and Italy, he returned, and made great progress in his stu- dies. In 1569, Allen invited him to Douay, to found there his English se- minary of idolatry and rebellion.
